<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/338> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #338" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Act. Tr. ([- - - - -]mus), Degrassi 95, 538, and Tab. 45." ;
	dprr:hasID 338 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/337> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #337" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "According to Degrassi (95) the broken letter preserved in Act. Tr. cannot be N and is clearly M. Accordingly the triumph listed there should not be attributed to the Dictator Mamercinus but to some other unnamed person. Degrassi (537) suggests the name given above, possibly a son of Maximus, Cos. 456 (Lactuca in Diod.) and father of Lactucinus Maximus, Mil. Tr. c. p. 398, and supposes that Geganius Macerinus abdicated. See also Degrassi, Epigraphica 1 (1939) 26ff." ;
	dprr:hasID 337 .
